On Easter Sunday, Christians celebrate the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead after his crucifixion and burial. It is typically the most well-attended Sunday church service of the year.

Key Takeaways: What Easter Means to Christians Christians believe, according to Scripture (Isaiah 53), that Jesus Christ is the promised Messiah and Savior of the World.

Jesus came back to life or was raised from the dead, three days after his death on the cross.
